node.text:
Looking for the perfect Instagram-worthy 1st Day of School photo? Follow along to DIY your own custom 1st Day of School Sign, using materials from @Michaelsstores! #sponsored⁣
⁣
The NEW Michaels Pro program is perfect for ordering arts and crafts supplies in bulk, and includes everything from party supplies to apparel, art supplies, and more! I transformed an unfinished wood pallet sign from the Michaels Pro line into this cute First Day of School sign! You’ll need:⁣
-unfinished wood pallet sign (from Michaels Pro)⁣
-wood planks⁣
-acrylic paint in yellow, pink, silver, tan, black and white ⁣
-paintbrushes⁣
-E-6000 glue⁣
-ribbon⁣
⁣
Customize your sign by adding your child’s name or the year/grade level! Tag me in your recreation so I can see it! Hope you have a great start to the new school year!⁣
⁣

node.text:
Ready to MAKE some magic in my new classroom soon! ✨ Classroom decorating is one of my favorite parts of back to school! I aim to create a space that is colorful, inspirational, and creates a routine for students to easily access the materials they need! 

I’m currently brainstorming how I want my students to enter the room and how they will get the materials they need without creating too much traffic in one area. 

Creating a routine is vital when you only have one- 40 minute period a week! You can lose a lot of time at the beginning or end of a class period without having a system in place. I have a routine in place for my littles, but I’d love to hear some upper elementary ideas! 💕⭐️
